Sentencas: Composites with nanostructured electrocatalyst or electrolyte particles usually exhibit highly electrochemical activity as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Composite Cathodes Consisting of Nanostructured LSM and SDC Particles

Sentencas: In this work, composites consisting of nanostructured (La0.85Sr0.15)(0.9)MnO3 (LSM) and nanostructured Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) particles are fabricated using an alternative impregnation method as SOFC cathodes.
Titulo: Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Composite Cathodes Consisting of Nanostructured LSM and SDC Particles

Sentencas: Scanning Electron Microscopy reveals that both LSM and SDC particles are less than 100 nm and uniformly distributed onto the inner surface of the porous LSM-SDC backbones.
Titulo: Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Composite Cathodes Consisting of Nanostructured LSM and SDC Particles

Sentencas: At 600 degrees C, the interfacial polarization resistance is only 0.93 Omega.cm(2) when stabilized zirconia is used as the electrolyte substrate.
Titulo: Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Composite Cathodes Consisting of Nanostructured LSM and SDC Particles

Sentencas: Anode-supported cells with the nanostructured LSM-SDC cathodes and zirconia-based electrolytes show peak power densities of 114, 218 and 348 mW.cm(-2) at 600, 650, and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Composite Cathodes Consisting of Nanostructured LSM and SDC Particles
